-- Nigeria’s Naira Moves Between Gains and Losses Against Dollar
-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 2012-03-08T14:19:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-08/nigeria-s-naira-moves-between-gains-and-losses-against-dollar.html
The naira moved between gains and
losses against the dollar.  The currency of Africa’s largest oil producer depreciated
less than 0.1 percent to 157.3975 per dollar as of 2:41 p.m. on
the  interbank market  in Lagos, the commercial capital. The naira
strengthened as much as 0.3 percent today and has gained 3.1
this year, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  The naira has been “broadly stable,”  Samir Gadio , an
emerging-markets strategist in London, said by e-mail today.  Ghana’s cedi appreciateed 0.1 percent to 1.7097 per dollar
in Accra, the capital.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chris Kay in Abuja at 
